excerpt: Aquarium with a stingray touch tank & shark tank plus manatees in the nearby mammal center.
detail_description: Mote Marine Laboratory & Aquarium is a fascinating destination that offers an immersive experience with over 100 marine species. Visitors can enjoy touch pools, working labs, and interactive exhibits. The aquarium features a stingray touch tank, a shark tank, and a nearby mammal center where manatees can be observed. Additionally, the facility provides educational opportunities for visitors of all ages to learn about marine life and interact with various sea creatures.
name: Mote Marine Laboratory & Aquarium
address: 1600 Ken Thompson Pkwy, Sarasota, FL 34236, USA

excerpt: State art museum founded by the circus magnate with 31 galleries in a pink Renaissance-style palace.
detail_description: The John and Mable Ringling Museum of Art is a state art museum established by the circus magnate, featuring 31 galleries housed in a pink Renaissance-style palace. Founded by John Ringling and his wife Mabel, the museum showcases over 10,000 items including European and American artworks, Asian art, contemporary pieces, decorative arts, and circus memorabilia. The building itself is an architectural attraction modeled after the Uffizi Gallery in Florence.
name: The John and Mable Ringling Museum of Art
address: 5401 Bay Shore Rd, Sarasota, FL 34243, USA

excerpt: Bayside showcase for tropical plants, plus a conservatory & garden museum, in a historic space.
detail_description: Marie Selby Botanical Gardens Downtown Sarasota is a 7-acre bayside showcase for tropical plants, featuring a conservatory and garden museum. It is dedicated to the research of orchids, epiphytes, and bromeliads. The gardens boast premier collections of native and tropical plants, trees, mosses, and colorful outdoor gardens.
name: Marie Selby Botanical Gardens Downtown Sarasota
address: 1534 Mound St, Sarasota, FL 34236, USA

excerpt: Boutiques, restaurants & salons set around a charming circular park with Italian statuary.
detail_description: St. Armands Circle is a charming circular park surrounded by boutiques, restaurants, and salons, featuring Italian statuary. The area is set to welcome new dining experiences like Bar Hana and Palm Avenue Deli, offering elevated bar food and classic comfort foods with a retro 1950s design. Visitors can explore over 100 shops and restaurants just steps away from Lido Beach or venture to nearby areas like Englewood's Dearborn Street or Venice Main Street.
name: St. Armands Circle
address: 300 Madison Dr, Sarasota, FL 34236, USA

excerpt: Venerable site showing 90+ classic, exotic & muscle cars, plus antique music boxes & phonographs.
detail_description: If you're looking for a unique experience in Sarasota, the Sarasota Classic Car Museum is an absolute must-visit. This remarkable museum, which holds the title of the second-oldest continuously operating classic car museum in the U.S., spans an impressive 60,000 square feet and showcases over 90 vintage vehicles.
name: Sarasota Classic Car Museum
address: 5500 N Tamiami Trl # B, Sarasota, FL 34243, USA

excerpt: Historic attraction featuring more than 150 animals & shows in a tropical setting.
detail_description: Sarasota Jungle Gardens is a historic attraction set in a tropical environment, showcasing over 150 animals and offering entertaining shows. Alongside other wildlife experiences in Sarasota County, such as the Mote Marine Laboratory & Aquarium and Myakka Elephant Ranch, visitors can interact with diverse marine species, care for elephants, and even participate in yoga sessions with foxes, lemurs, and tigers at the Big Cat Habitat & Gulf Coast Sanctuary.
name: Sarasota Jungle Gardens
address: 3701 Bay Shore Rd, Sarasota, FL 34234, USA

detail_description: If you're looking for a vibrant slice of local life, the Sarasota Farmers Market is an absolute must-visit! This weekly event takes place in downtown Sarasota and showcases over 70 vendors offering everything from fresh fruits and vegetables to artisanal baked goods and unique crafts. The market not only provides a fantastic shopping experience but also features live music, cooking demonstrations, and activities that are perfect for families.
name: Sarasota Farmers Market
address: N Lemon Ave, Sarasota, FL 34236, USA

excerpt: Housed in an ornate circa-1926 theater, this facility mounts familiar & unusual opera productions.
detail_description: The Sarasota Opera House, a historic theater dating back to 1926, is a vibrant cultural hub in downtown Sarasota. It showcases a diverse range of opera productions, concerts, and events while also offering educational programs and community outreach initiatives. The upcoming season promises an exciting lineup of six opera productions, including classics like Cavalleria Rusticana/Pagliacci and The Barber of Seville. Additionally, the venue collaborates with the Sarasota Orchestra and hosts acclaimed youth opera productions.
name: Sarasota Opera House
address: 61 N Pineapple Ave, Sarasota, FL 34236, USA

excerpt: Sandy beach featuring a concession stand, gift shop & picnic tables, plus a swimming pool.
detail_description: Lido Key Beach is a picturesque sandy beach that offers various amenities such as a concession stand, gift shop, and picnic tables. It is located in Sarasota, Florida, known for its stunning beaches with powdery white sands and clear waters ideal for swimming and water sports. Lido Key Beach is situated near Siesta Key Beach, which is renowned for its soft quartz sand and calm waters, making it perfect for families.
name: Lido Key Beach
address: 400 Benjamin Franklin Dr, Sarasota, FL 34236, USA

excerpt: Waterfront green space with a promenade, playground, tiki bar & dramatic views of the bay & city.
detail_description: Bayfront Park is a picturesque waterfront green space located in Sarasota, just across the road from downtown. It offers a serene oasis with a promenade, playground, and tiki bar, as well as stunning views of the bay and city. Visitors can enjoy a leisurely waterfront walk or have a picnic under the beautiful banyan trees. The park also provides access to Marina Jack, where multimillion-dollar yachts are moored and fine dining options are available.
name: Bayfront Park
address: 5 Bayfront Dr, Sarasota, FL 34236, USA

excerpt: Cheerful gallery featuring offbeat, contemporary paintings, sculpture & other artwork.
detail_description: The Marietta Museum of Art & Whimsy in Sarasota is a vibrant and cheerful gallery dedicated to celebrating the creative human spirit through whimsical art. Founded by artist Marietta Lee, this museum features an eclectic collection of contemporary paintings, sculptures, and mixed-media artwork that exude brightness and color. The outdoor sculpture garden adds to the playful atmosphere with unique installations like hanging simians and a giant flamingo wearing a top hat.
name: Marietta Museum of Art & Whimsy
address: 2121 N Tamiami Trl, Sarasota, FL 34234, USA

excerpt: 1,736-seat bayfront institution presents concerts spanning classical to jazz plus Broadway musicals.
detail_description: Nestled along the picturesque Sarasota Bay, the Van Wezel Performing Arts Hall is a stunning 1,736-seat venue that serves as a cultural hub for the community. Designed by the renowned Frank Lloyd Wright's Taliesin Foundation, its unique purple seashell architecture makes it an iconic landmark. The hall hosts an impressive array of performances throughout the year, including Broadway musicals, classical concerts, jazz shows, and dance troupes.
name: Van Wezel Performing Arts Hall
address: 777 N Tamiami Trl, Sarasota, FL 34236, USA

excerpt: Casual, beachy spot with a covered patio offering seafood & bar fare, draft beer & live music.
detail_description: Siesta Key Oyster Bar, affectionately known as S.K.O.B., is a laid-back beach spot with a covered patio where you can savor delicious seafood and bar favorites while enjoying draft beer and live music. The restaurant lives up to its name by offering an array of fresh oysters and other local seafood dishes. From raw and baked oysters to grouper bites with signature remoulade, there's something for every seafood lover.
name: Siesta Key Oyster Bar
address: 5238 Ocean Blvd, Sarasota, FL 34242, USA

excerpt: Seafood spot with an outdoor raw bar patio, upstairs dining room, piano bar & expansive water views.
detail_description: Marina Jack is a popular seafood spot in downtown Sarasota, offering both upscale and casual dining experiences with beautiful waterfront views. The Blue Sunshine Patio provides diners with a scenic experience right on Sarasota Bay next to docked yachts, while the second floor dining room offers panoramic water views. The Deep Six Lounge also features outdoor seating for guests to enjoy lunch and dinner. The menu includes popular dishes such as grilled grouper, potato-crusted grouper, and baked oysters Rockefeller.
name: Marina Jack
address: 2 Marina Plaza, Sarasota, FL 34236, USA

detail_description: As you stroll back over the bridge, make sure to stop by the iconic Unconditional Surrender statue, a stunning tribute that captures a moment from history. This larger-than-life bronze sculpture is inspired by the famous photograph of a sailor kissing a nurse in Times Square on V-J Day in 1945. While artist Seward Johnson drew inspiration from this well-known image, he also referenced another lesser-known photo taken at that moment.
name: Unconditional Surrender
address: Sarasota, FL 34236, USA

excerpt: This barrier island connected to the mainland via a causeway features beaches, a park & nightlife.
detail_description: Lido Key is a barrier island connected to the mainland by a causeway, offering beautiful beaches, a park, and vibrant nightlife. The area is renowned for its luxurious resorts and access to upscale shopping and dining at St. Armands Circle and Longboat Key. Visitors can enjoy staying at hotels like Lido Beach Resort and Zota Beach Resort, both providing fine dining, ocean-view swimming pools, private cabanas, and other lavish amenities.
name: Lido Key
address: Sarasota, FL 34236, USA

excerpt: 18th-century Italian-style theater offering classic & Broadway works by the house repertory company.
detail_description: Asolo Repertory Theatre, an 18th-century Italian-style theater located near the Ringling Museum of Art, offers classic and Broadway works performed by its house repertory company. The venue provides cultural entertainment with inspirational performances in a comfortable and accessible setting. Equipped with a hearing loop system, it ensures rich auditory immersion for all patrons.
name: Asolo Repertory Theatre
address: 5555 N Tamiami Trl, Sarasota, FL 34243, USA

excerpt: Once home to the Ringlings, this circa-1924 mansion draws inspiration from the palazzos of Venice.
detail_description: Ca' d'Zan, the winter residence of John and Mable Ringling, is a stunning mansion in Sarasota that exudes luxury and elegance. Built in 1924 by architect Dwight James Baum, this Mediterranean Revival mansion draws inspiration from the palazzos of Venice with its Venetian Gothic style architecture. The five-story waterfront mansion boasts 56 rooms filled with European influences and meticulous design.
name: Ca' d'Zan
address: 5401 Bay Shore Rd, Sarasota, FL 34243, USA

detail_description: Nestled in Florida, the Westcoast Black Theatre Troupe stands out as one of only three professional black theaters in the state. Celebrating its 25th anniversary, this vibrant troupe is dedicated to showcasing African American history and culture through dynamic performances. The theme for this milestone season is '25 Years of Black Heritage,' featuring a mix of beloved adaptations and original works crafted by their talented ensemble of singers, actors, and dancers.
name: Westcoast Black Theatre Troupe
address: 1012 N Orange Ave, Sarasota, FL 34236, USA

excerpt: Ringling Circus archives, with historical documents, costume drawings & art (by appointment).
detail_description: Tibbals Learning Center and Circus Museum at The Ringling is a treasure trove of circus history, offering a glimpse into the world of the Ringling Brothers Circus. Visitors can explore historical documents, costume drawings, and art by appointment. The museum showcases the unique relationship between John Ringling, the circus, and the Sarasota area through exhibits like the world's largest Circus Miniature and John and Mable Ringling's private Pullman train car.
name: Tibbals Learning Center & Circus Museum at The Ringling
address: 5401 Bay Shore Rd, Sarasota, FL 34243, USA
